        </p>

        <h3>How the Direct Nomination Works</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <strong>Health Authority Identifies Need:</strong> The HR department identifies positions that cannot be filled domestically and opens them to international recruitment.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Recruitment and Selection:</strong> The health authority recruits internationally, often partnering with agencies or attending job fairs abroad to identify qualified candidates.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Job Offer Extension:</strong> Once a suitable candidate is identified, the health authority extends a formal job offer meeting BC PNP requirements (full-time, indeterminate).
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Employer Registration:</strong> The health authority registers as an approved employer in the BC PNP system if not already registered.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Immigration Support Letter:</strong> The employer provides documentation confirming the job offer, salary, duties, and the candidate's qualifications.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Candidate Applies:</strong> With employer support documentation, the candidate registers in SIRS and submits their BC PNP application upon invitation.
          </li>
        </ol>

