        </p>

        <h3>Step 1: Secure a Qualifying Job Offer</h3>
        <p>
          Your journey begins with obtaining a full-time, indeterminate (permanent) job offer from an eligible BC public health authority. The job offer must meet these requirements:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Minimum 30 hours per week</li>
          <li>No fixed end date (indeterminate)</li>
          <li>Located in British Columbia</li>
          <li>Wage meets or exceeds median wage for the occupation</li>
          <li>From an eligible public health authority employer</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Step 2: Begin Professional Licensing</h3>
        <p>
          Most healthcare occupations in BC are <strong>regulated professions</strong>. You must be registered or eligible for registration with the appropriate BC regulatory body before you can work. Start this process early as it can take 3-12 months.
